cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE

This paper is about training distributed word representations for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of large corpora and pre-trained models, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the word vectors using analogy datasets and comparison with previous models involves performance evaluation (cs.IR) and optimization (cs.NE) techniques.
